

The numbers are placed on a hexagonal “point‑top’’ lattice in an anticlockwise spiral.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1.   Geometry of the spiral  

Let the centre be the origin \((0,0)\) and use the axial coordinates  

\[
(q,r)\quad\text{with neighbours}\qquad
\begin{array}{l}
E:(+1,0)\\
NE:(+1,-1)\\
NW:(0,-1)\\
W:(-1,0)\\
SW:(-1,+1)\\
SE:(0,+1)
\end{array}
\]

The distance from the centre is  

\[
d(q,r)=\frac{|q|+|r|+|q+r|}{2}.
\]

For a given “ring’’ \(d\ge 1\) the cells with distance \(d\) are exactly the
\(6d\) cells on that ring.  
The last number of ring \(d\) is  

\[
N_d = 1+3d(d+1),
\]

hence the first number of ring \(d\) is  

\[
S_d = N_{d-1}+1 = 3d(d-1)+2 .
\]

The spiral begins each new ring to the east of the previous ring, i.e. the
first cell of ring \(d\) has coordinates  

\[
P_d=(1,\;d-1) .
\]

From the start point the anticlockwise walk proceeds

* north‑east steps (vector \((+1,-1)\)) – \(d-1\) steps – reaching the east‑corner
\((d,0)\);
* then the five sides of the hexagon, each of length \(d\):
  north‑west \((0,-1)\), west \((-1,0)\), south‑west \((-1,+1)\),
  south‑east \((0,+1)\), east \((+1,0)\).

Hence for a point on ring \(d\) its offset \(k\) from the start of the ring
(the first number of the ring is offset 0) can be found as follows.

*If \(q+r=d\) and \(q\ge 1\)                                
\(\displaystyle k = q-1.\)

Otherwise the point lies on one of the five sides.  
For the west side \((r=-d,\;0\le q\le d-1)\)

\[
k = 2d-1 \;+\;(d-q) = 3d-q-1 .
\]

(Analogous formulas exist for the other sides, but only the west side will be
needed here.)

The number at \((q,r)\) is \(N = S_d + k\).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2.   Which ring contains 2026?

Find \(d\) with  

\[
S_d\le 2026\le N_d .
\]

\[
N_{25}=1+3\cdot25\cdot26=1951,\qquad 
N_{26}=1+3\cdot26\cdot27=2107 .
\]

Thus \(d=26\) (the 26‑th ring).  
The first number of this ring is  

\[
S_{26}=3\cdot26\cdot25+2=1952 .
\]

The offset of 2026 inside ring 26 is  

\[
k = 2026-1952 = 74 .
\]

Since \(k> d-1 (=25)\) the number is not on the initial north‑east segment.
It lies on the **west side** (\(r=-d\)).  
Using the west‑side formula  

\[
k = 3d-q-1\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
74 = 3\cdot26 - q -1 \;\Longrightarrow\; q=3 .
\]

Hence  

\[
\boxed{(q,r)=(3,\,-26)} .
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3.   The six neighbours of \((3,-26)\)

Applying the neighbour vectors:

\[
\begin{aligned}
E &: (4,-26)\\
NE&: (4,-27)\\
NW&: (3,-27)\\
W &: (2,-26)\\
SW&: (2,-25)\\
SE&: (3,-25)
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4.   Numbers on the neighbour cells  

*On the same ring 26 (west side):*  

\[
\begin{aligned}
(4,-26)&:\; k = 3\cdot26-4-1 = 73 \;\Longrightarrow\; 1952+73 = 2025 ,\\
(2,-26)&:\; k = 3\cdot26-2-1 = 75 \;\Longrightarrow\; 1952+75 = 2027 .
\end{aligned}
\]

*On the outer ring 27 (again west side, \(r=-27\)):*  

\[
\begin{aligned}
(4,-27)&:\; k = 3\cdot27-4-1 = 76 \;\Longrightarrow\; 2108+76 = 2184 ,\\
(3,-27)&:\; k = 3\cdot27-3-1 = 77 \;\Longrightarrow\; 2108+77 = 2185 .
\end{aligned}
\]

*On the inner ring 25 (west side, \(r=-25\)):*  

\[
\begin{aligned}
(3,-25)&:\; k = 3\cdot25-3-1 = 71 \;\Longrightarrow\; 1802+71 = 1873 ,\\
(2,-25)&:\; k = 3\cdot25-2-1 = 72 \;\Longrightarrow\; 1802+72 = 1874 .
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5.   Sum of the six neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum} &= 2025+2027+2184+2185+1873+1874 \\
          &= (2025+2027)+(2184+2185)+(1873+1874)\\
          &= 4052+4369+3747\\
          &= 12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
----
